tool.name: MapOutline

param.name: SE_longitude
param.dialogReference: Longitude of SE corner of map rectangle. May be in decimal degrees (-120.625), degrees - decimal minutes (-120 37.5) or degrees - minutes - seconds (-120 37 30). West longitudes (all of US) are negative.

param.name: SE_latitude
param.dialogReference: Latitude of SE corner of map rectangle. May be in decimal degrees (42.375), degrees - decimal minutes (42 22.5) or degrees - minutes - seconds (48 22 30). South latitudes (none in US) are negative.

param.name: width__longitudinal_extent_
param.dialogReference: E-W extent of map rectangle. Values <= 5 are assumed to be in degrees. Values >5 are assumed to be in minutes. Enter 600 to obtain a 10 degree extent.

param.name: height__latitudinal_extent_
param.dialogReference: N-S extent of map rectangle. Values <= 5 are assumed to be in degrees. Values >5 are assumed to be in minutes. Enter 600 to obtain a 10 degree extent.

param.name: tic_spacing
param.dialogReference: Value is in decimal minutes.

param.name: Is_NAD27
param.dialogReference: Check to locate map boundary and tics at NAD27 lat-long positions. Uncheck to locate at NAD83 positions.

param.name: output_geodatabase
param.dialogReference: Must be an existing, writable geodatabase. Please do not select a feature dataset or feature class (though ArcGIS will let you do so).

param.name: output_coordinate_system
param.dialogReference: Browse to select coordinate system from ArcGIS-provided coordinate system definitions, to import a coordinate system from an existing data set (RECOMMENDED) or define a coordinate system from scratch.

param.name: scratch_workspace
param.dialogReference: Directory that is writable. Files xxxbox.csv, xxxtics.csv, xxx1.dbf, xxx1.dbf.xml will be written to this directory and then deleted. Existing files with these names will be lost!

tool.summary:
Calculates map boundary and tics for rectangular (in lat-long space) areas. Boundaries and tics may be in NAD27 or NAD83, and are projected to output coordinate system.

Output feature classes MapOutline and Tics are written to top level of output geodatabase. Any existing feature classes with these names will be overwritten.
